Quote:  `Freyberg's Circus' (as the troops often called it) was maintained as much by rank-and-file laughter, horseplay, mischief, and the assertive, rumbunctious, enterprising spirits of autonomous man as it was by any subservience to conventional military organisation or to aspirations of professionalism.
